summary: An FBI 302 report documenting an interview conducted on July 31, 2019, with an individual at the NYPD's 13th Precinct in Long Island City, Queens. The interviewee denied knowing Jeffrey Epstein when shown his photograph and provided a personal timeline of residence in Queens, Brazil, San Diego, and New York.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The interviewee was shown a photograph of Epstein and stated she did not know him.

events.title: FBI Interview at NYPD Precinct
events.description: An FBI agent interviewed an individual at the NYPD's 13th Precinct in Long Island City, Queens, regarding knowledge of Jeffrey Epstein.

locations: New York Police Department's 13th Precinct, Long Island City - Queens, New York
keyFacts: An individual was interviewed by the FBI on July 31, 2019, in connection with the Jeffrey Epstein investigation.
The interviewee denied knowing Jeffrey Epstein when shown his photograph.
The interviewee lived in Queens, NY, between approximately 2001-2001, returned to Brazil, then came back to the U.S., lived in San Diego, and returned to New York in 2005.
The document is an FBI 302 report, indicating it is a summary of an investigative interview and contains neither recommendations nor conclusions.
